Standard templates are very useful. However, Confluence needs the ability to associate a specific template with a child relationship, so that 'add child' uses the template without extra user effort. Maybe there could be two options so that you can either make a specific template the default or mandatory? This would enable a style to be applied consistently to various areas of the wiki.

It would be cool if, when writing code, Confluence could link up classes to their Javadocs. Eg.:

{code}
JiraSoapService server = new JiraSoapService();
{code}

becomes:

[JiraSoapService|http://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/rpc-jira-plugin/latest/com/atlassian/jira/rpc/soap/JiraSoapService.html] server = new JiraSoapService();

